CDFglobalAttributes.Descriptor: epead-science-electrons-e13ew>Energetic Proton Electron and Alpha Detector Reprocessed Electron Fluxes for Science Use
CDFglobalAttributes.TEXT: Data has been recast from original NOAA netCDF files by SPDF. DATA CAVEATS/WARNINGS:integral electron flux corrected and flagged using complete set of Sauer coefficients and flagged when data are bad due to solar proton contamination; channel E3 not included in this version.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Date and time for each observation (beginning of the minute over which the data are averaged)
VarAttributes.Long_Name: Date and time for each observation (beginning of the minute over which the data are averaged)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: EPEAD orientation flag. 0: A/W faces East and B/E faces West. 1: A/W faces West and B/E faces East. 2: yaw-flip in progress.
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: EPEAD orientation flag (0: A/W faces East and B/E faces West. 1: A/W faces West and B/E faces East. 2: yaw-flip in progress.)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >.8 MeV from the A detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = east 1 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) corrected for dead time

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >.8 MeV from the B detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (1 = east 0 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) corrected for dead time

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >2 MeV from the A detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = east 1 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) corrected for dead time

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >2 MeV from the B detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (1 = east 0 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) corrected for dead time

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >.8 MeV from the A detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = east 1 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination and dead-time corrected (or fluxes replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >.8 MeV from the B detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = west 1 = east 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination and dead-time corrected (or fluxes replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >2 MeV from the A detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = east 1 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination and dead-time corrected (or fluxes replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Average flux of electrons with energy >2 MeV from the B detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = west 1 = east 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination and dead-time corrected (or fluxes replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Standard deviation, electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Standard deviation, electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Standard deviation (fractional) of average flux of electrons with energy >.8 MeV from the A detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = east 1 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination corrected (replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Standard deviation, electron integral flux E1 >0.8 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Standard deviation (fractional) of average flux of electrons with energy >.8 MeV from the B detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = west 1 = east 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination corrected (replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Standard deviation, electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Standard deviation, electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Standard deviation (fractional) of average flux of electrons with energy >2 MeV from the A detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = east 1 = west 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination corrected (replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Standard deviation, electron integral flux E2 >2 MeV (background, contamination and dead time corrected)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Standard deviation (fractional) of average flux of electrons with energy >2 MeV from the B detector that faces East or West depending on the orientation flag (0 = west 1 = east 2 = yaw-flip in progress) with backgrounds removed and proton contamination corrected (replaced with fill values if contamination is too severe)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy E1 >.8 MeV (0 if contamination is sufficiently small that the correction and electron fluxes are valid; 1 if contamination is too large and the electron fluxes are not valid.)
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy E1 >.8 MeV (0 if contamination is sufficiently small that the correction and electron fluxes are valid; 1 if contamination is too large and the electron fluxes are not valid.)
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy >.8 MeV from the A detector:  0 if contamination is sufficiently small that the correction and electron fluxes are valid 1 if contamination is too large and the electron fluxes are not valid.

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy E1 >.8 MeV
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy >.8 MeV from the B detector:  0 if contamination is sufficiently small that the correction and electron fluxes are valid 1 if contamination is too large and the electron fluxes are not valid.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A/W Detector: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy E2 >2 MeV
VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: A/W Detector: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy E2 >2 MeV
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy >2 MeV from the A detector:  0 if contamination is sufficiently small that the correction and electron fluxes are valid 1 if contamination is too large and the electron fluxes are not valid.  (Note: if the flag is set to 1 intermittently throughout an extended period either the contamination correction is borderline too large or the fluxes are close to backgrounds and should be treated with caution.

VarAttributes.FULL_CATDESC: B/E Detector: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy E2 >2 MeV
VarAttributes.DESCRIP: Data quality flag pertaining to solar proton contamination for fluxes with energy >2 MeV from the B detector:  0 if contamination is sufficiently small that the correction and electron fluxes are valid 1 if contamination is too large and the electron fluxes are not valid.  (Note: if the flag is set to 1 intermittently throughout an extended period either the contamination correction is borderline too large or the fluxes are close to backgrounds and should be treated with caution.
